					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/comparing-realities" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2503657); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2503657&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164528" alt="Comparing Realities" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2503657)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/comparing-realities" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2503657); return false;" >Comparing Realities</a></span> <span class="odate time_1492310470 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Apr 2017 02:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2792935">
									

<blockquote>
<p>PoI-3000-1: Yes, I put it on his belly and told him he could eat it and the freezer is good because the cold numbs the belly and it makes the meat harder and slippery for the knife and I knew how sharp the knife was, it was like a trick but it wasn't a mean trick&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I have never—and I mean <em>never</em>—felt quite the way you made me feel right there. What most people say is horror, I only read as &quot;interesting bad things&quot;. I think I've been anesthetized by the sheer bad-thing creativity on this site. But to be brought back to reality for a moment, to realize that <em>this could actually happen</em> and that worse things have been done in the past&#8230;</p>

							</div>

								
