			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2789463">
									

<p>To start - Upvote, this was some great stuff. I really enjoyed the ambiguity of the potential horror without needing anomalies.</p>
<p>But, this brings up an interesting question. For me, this feels more like a report that would declare these objects non-anomalous, rather than an SCP-EX article.</p>
<p>Nothing of that is a knock to you, this is great writing, but maybe this needs another format. Something like a Proposal for SCP Designation, which was rejected, with a similar format to an SCP article?</p>
<p>I say that, because my feeling is that this object wouldn't have ever actually made it on the list. It never got past the &quot;Possibly anomalous&quot; stage.</p>
<p>Also, bonus points for including a new GoI.</p>

