			<div class="content" id="post-content-2789511">
									

<p>I really dug this one, first. So you get a shiny +1 from me.</p>
<p>I don't buy that this situation was cataloged as an SCP phenomenon in the first place, though. It's creepy and gross and unfortunate, but at no point do I see where the Foundation would have marked this multiple murder situation, tragic as it was, as a full-blown anomaly. Sure, some people thought that maybe the beds did something, and maybe the Fifthists were possibly involved, but I have to belive that the Foundation would put more research in before delegating an SCP slot to this.</p>

