			<div class="content" id="post-content-2789879">
									

<p>I once started work on a tale based on this idea. A few excerpts:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;One</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Item #: PAC-21684</p>
<p>Provisional Object Class: Euclid</p>
<p>Interim Containment Procedures: [Not Yet Defined]</p>
<p>Description: PAC-21684 is &quot;The Grey Towers&quot;, an Estonian daytime soap opera which no one has ever seen. It is broadcast each Monday at 14:00 on the Kanal 1 channel, each episode running for 58 minutes including advertising breaks.</p>
<p>Audience research has consistently failed to find anyone who recalls seeing more than several seconds of the programme. Some remember seeing it mentioned in TV listings, and a few admit to having channel surfed past it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Two</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>PAC - &quot;Potential Anomalous Classification&quot;. It's what we call things that <em>might</em> be SCPs, before we decide whether they <em>are</em> or not. There's been hundreds of thousands over the years - some turn out to be hoaxes, more are urban legends, a few are the real deal&#8230;and some we just never figure out.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Three</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A diamond engagement ring that's been involved in 17 consecutive broken marriages. Anomaly, or sign of the times? PAC-12779, still undetermined.</p>
<p>An infectious but symptomless virus that's been passed among at least 103 people, every one of who eventually dies in a peanut butter related accident. Cosmic joke, or bug in the monitoring software? PAC-10074.</p>
<p>A recipe for root beer that when recited backwards opens a portal to a parallel world ruled by sentient sloths. The recipe is PAC-371, the portal is PAC-371-1 and the world is PAC-371-2. Except it hasn't worked since 1854, so no one's interested in resuming research.</p>
<p>PAC-87855. A woman who has been abducted by at least three serial killers, and each time escaped. The unluckiest woman in the world? The luckiest victim? Generator of serial killers?</p>
<p>PAC-44113. A pair of doors that only let white people unlock them. They used to belong to a golf club.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
